cs.PF, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS

The paper discusses benchmarking different parallel programming frameworks for heterogeneous computing systems. This topic falls under the area of performance evaluation and optimization of computer systems, which is covered by the cs.PF sub-category. The paper also involves empirical studies and experiments, which are typical of the cs.AR (Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the energy consumption and performance of the frameworks, which are relevant to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories.
